{"id":14881446,"mediaExerciseId":"5548b591-cae8-419c-9583-f511a4062ae3","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612387,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":487,"solutions":[{"id":5980160,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Since the interest paid on a company's debt is tax-deductible, after-tax costs are taken into account when calculating debt, as a consequence, the tax effect just on the net cost of capital must be eliminated completely.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/656a7daa814d1728d320766013fc31e4/3bc62dd8f783e4506530638a6de7fa2f/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/656a7daa814d1728d320766013fc31e4/3bc62dd8f783e4506530638a6de7fa2f/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"However, because dividends are paid from the earnings earned by the business's operational activities, dividends paid on equity or capital gains from equity are not tax-deductible, as a consequence, because cost equity has no impact on pre-or post-tax costs, and do not need to change the cost of equity by the tax rate.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":174,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/656a7daa814d1728d320766013fc31e4/c04056a4815dfae842c54d6cf0940d8b/lateximg_large.png","width":1023},"regular":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/656a7daa814d1728d320766013fc31e4/c04056a4815dfae842c54d6cf0940d8b/lateximg.png","width":511}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"2feb01eb-0feb-4b6b-a75f-d4ba0492113b","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":nul